author: the Messenger-Inquirer
title: Lady Raiders win volleyball district title
text:
Lady Raiders win volleyball district title By the Messenger-Inquirer 0 
The Whitesville Trinity volleyball team has now won five district championships in a row. 
The Lady Raiders continued their run by dispatching Edmonson County in four sets (21-25, 25-18, 25-18, 26-24) in the 12th District Tournament title game on Thursday night in Whitesville. 
Katelyn Coomes led Trinity (11-14) with 20 kills and three blocks. Savannah Aull added 13 kills and five aces, while Alanna Wathen finished with 40 assists and 26 digs. Haley Payne had 31 digs and three aces, Abby Booker added eight kills, Shelby Aud had 18 digs, and Molli Buck chipped in three aces. 
Both teams will advance to the 3rd Region Volleyball Tournament. Ã—
